      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> potatoes </strong>into bite-sized pieces, then add them to a heatproof bowl and cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong></p><p>Pierce a few holes in the top with a fork, then put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>or until the potatoes are tender</p>",
